- cs.PF (Performance): The paper deals with scheduling jobs on a heterogeneous multiprocessor with the objective of minimizing weighted flow plus energy, which is a performance-related problem. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with scheduling jobs on a multiprocessor, which can be seen as a control problem in systems engineering. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes an algorithm for scheduling jobs, which can be seen as a machine learning problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper deals with optimizing the flow of data on a multiprocessor, which can be seen as an information theory problem.
